“**The Nautilus Navigator: A Bio-Acoustic Reef Sanctuary**” – A wearable device, resembling a polished nautilus shell, that actively ‘listens’ to and responds to the complex sonic communication of coral reefs. Utilizing advanced AI, it translates the fish, invertebrate, and algal soundscapes into targeted, multi-frequency acoustic stimulation delivered directly to the reef via an underwater transducer. Simultaneously, the shell monitors the user's biometric data (stress levels, heart rate variability) and subtly adjusts the stimulation in real-time, creating a deeply personalized “reef sanctuary” experience. Users can even ‘upload’ their own calming music or guided meditations to be subtly interwoven into the sonic tapestry! It’s a way to *literally* become part of the reef's ecosystem, fostering both coral resilience and a profoundly meditative experience. The shell includes haptic feedback to simulate the feeling of current and subtle water movement, enhancing the immersive effect. Think biofeedback meets marine biology meets…well, me!